description:
&lt;p&gt;Would you like to start an exciting career in the NHS, learning new skills and knowledge of Grounds and Gardens, whilst achieving a nationally recognised apprenticeship qualification?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you want a paid job with great prospects to grow &amp; develop your skills?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Everyone who joins our Trust is given every opportunity to increase skills and confidence through training and development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to recruit an apprentice in a Grounds and Garden Operative role to develop within our organisation. Apprentices must be over the age of 18.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will provide excellent customer services and the role will involve a range of duties to ensure the smooth running of the organisation. Your role will maintain a high standard of professionalism and provide services in line with our values and behaviours.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be employed on a fixed term contract for 2 years whilst undertaking your apprenticeship and work 37.5 hours per week - Monday to Friday.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are great benefits to undertaking an apprenticeship. Through your apprenticeship with us you will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Earn a salary&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Get valuable and practical work experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gain new skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Achieve nationally recognised qualifications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work alongside and learn from our highly skilled and knowledgeable staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Get ongoing help and support from colleagues as well as a dedicated mentor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be able to enjoy our fantastic employee benefits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Kick start your new career within one the UK&#39;s most valued institutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The apprenticeship scheme is run in partnership with local training providers and is delivered in the workplace and through on-line learning in conjunction with the YMCA. You will attend a planned induction and additional training events and given time to complete your studies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is subject to a standard Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) Check. Successful candidates will either have a valid DBS check with the Trust or will be required to pay for the cost of the DBS Disclosure which is £29.50, the cost of which will be deducted from first salary&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Anthony Whittaker - Hard FM Estates Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;anthony.whittaker@nwbh.nhs.uk / 01925 664000&lt;/p&gt;
